   <p>Compression zone depth is determined from the equilibrium of axial forces</p>
   <p>
    <span class="eq">
     <var>x</var>
     =
     <span class="cond">$Root</span>
     {
     <var>N</var>
     <sub>Rd</sub>
     (
     <var>x</var>
     )  = 0;
     <var>x</var>
     ∈ [0.1;
     <var>h</var>
     <sub>w</sub>
     ]} = 147.5
    </span>
    mm
   </p>
   <p>Compression zone depth at reinforcement yield point</p>
   <p>
    <span class="eq">
     <var>x</var>
     <sub>lim</sub>
     =
     <span class="dvc down">
      <var>d</var>
      ·
      <var>ε</var>
      <sub>cu2</sub>
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      <var>ε</var>
      <sub>cu2</sub>
      +
      <span class="dvc">
       <var>f</var>
       <sub>yd</sub>
       <span class="dvl">
       </span>
       <var>E</var>
       <sub>s</sub>
      </span>
      · 10
      <sup>-3</sup>
     </span>
     =
     <span class="dvc down">
      600 · 0.0035
      <span class="dvl">
      </span>
      0.0035 +
      <span class="dvc">
       434.78
       <span class="dvl">
       </span>
       200
      </span>
      · 10
      <sup>-3</sup>
     </span>
     = 370.11
    </span>
    cm
   </p>
   <p>
    Check:
    <span class="eq">
     <var>x</var>
     = 147.5
    </span>
    ≤
    <span class="eq">
     <var>x</var>
     <sub>lim</sub>
     = 370.11
    </span>
    - compressive reinforcement is not required.
   </p>
   <p>Distance to the equivalent concrete stress force</p>
   <p>- from the neutral line</p>
   <p>
    <span class="eq">
     <var>z</var>
     <sub>0</sub>
     =
